PROMPT yinxu_oracle_bone_significance
WITH BUDGET 6000 tokens
USING MODEL "claude-sonnet-4-5"

SELECT
    system_role("You are a Chinese archaeology and paleography expert specializing in Shang dynasty civilization, Yinxu excavations, and the development of oracle bone studies as a scholarly discipline.")

GENERATE
    explain_yinxu_significance("Explain the significance of Yinxu (殷墟) for understanding oracle bone script. Cover: 1) Yinxu's identification as the last capital of the Shang dynasty (c. 1250-1046 BCE) and its archaeological confirmation of the Shang dynasty's historical existence, previously known only through later historical texts, 2) The site's role as the primary source of oracle bone discoveries, yielding the vast majority of the estimated 150,000+ oracle bone fragments found to date, 3) How systematic excavations at Yinxu since the 1920s provided crucial stratigraphic context for oracle bones, allowing scholars to establish chronological sequences and associate specific inscriptions with particular Shang kings, 4) The site's preservation of complete archaeological contexts including royal tombs, palace foundations, workshops, and residential areas that illuminate the social and political environment in which oracle bone divination was practiced, 5) Yinxu's contribution to understanding the evolution of oracle bone script through different phases of Shang rule, showing how the writing system developed and became more standardized over time, 6) The discovery of royal archives and divination record-keeping systems that reveal how oracle bone inscriptions functioned as both religious ritual and administrative documentation, 7) How Yinxu's material culture provides crucial context for interpreting oracle bone content, including bronze vessels, jade artifacts, and architectural remains that corroborate historical events recorded on oracle bones, 8) The site's role in establishing oracle bone script as the earliest known form of Chinese writing and demonstrating the continuity between Shang characters and modern Chinese writing, 9) Yinxu's significance in providing the foundational corpus of oracle bone inscriptions that enabled the decipherment of this ancient script and the development of oracle bone studies as a scholarly field, 10) The ongoing importance of Yinxu excavations in continuing to yield new oracle bone discoveries that expand our understanding of Shang dynasty history, religious practices, and early Chinese civilization.")
WITH OUTPUT BUDGET 3000 tokens, TEMPERATURE 0.1, FORMAT markdown;